{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we walked from-- from Brunnlitz towards Krakow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we wound up in places that we should have never been.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were just totally off the map for where we were going.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after numerous days, maybe as many as seven days, we arrived in the city of Wroclaw.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The 17 of us, in relatively good health by now-- the way we fed ourselves is by stopping off at farmers' and begging for food and, if necessary, stealing food.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The only danger we faced was from the Russians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Russians had absolutely no heart for the people that were wanderers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so we were in danger with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Well, I also have to back off now to-- to get back to the-- when Schindler left the camp and left us alone.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Is that-- as Schindler predicted and told us on May 8, 1945, a single Russian soldier marched into our camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he was walking by a horse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That horse, at that time, when I first saw him, appeared like a little donkey.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the Russian soldier appeared like a 20-foot tall man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This was all-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] just the moment created such a mirage that I saw things that never happened.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "When Schindler declared that the war is ended, the-- the cries and laughs and the push of the inmates toward Schindler to kiss his feet, to kiss his hands, to hug him, to squeeze him, were-- resulted in a totally indescribable situation.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I mean, it was-- it was like something that you would-- you'll never see again in your life, what happened then, the reaction of people that we are finally free people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But Schindler left us, and as I started telling, we left on that trip.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
